  "market_context": "Bearish market structure confirmed by valid break of structure below a major low at 1.07400. Price had just completed a strong bearish impulse move and was in a corrective retracement phase.",
  "key_observation": "An unmitigated Fair Value Gap (FVG) was identified at the extreme of the recent bearish impulse move; price later retraced upward to fill this gap before resuming its bearish momentum.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Confirmed dominant bearish market structure via a valid Break of Structure (BOS) below the major swing low at 1.07400.",
    "Step 2: Analyzed the chart from top to bottom (per bearish convention) to locate FVGs within the recent bearish impulse move.",
    "Step 3: Identified a three-candle sequence at the market extreme and drew lines from the lower wick of the first candle and upper wick of the third candle to reveal an unmitigated FVG.",
    "Step 4: Noted another potential FVG formed by a four-candle sequence (mother candle + three candles), but confirmed it was mitigated and thus not tradable.",
    "Step 5: Observed that only one unmitigated FVG remained at the extreme, which price was expected to retrace into and fill before continuing downward.",
    "Step 6: Later confirmed price did retrace up, filled the unmitigated FVG, then reversed and resumed bearish momentum."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retraced to fill the unmitigated FVG and then continued downward, validating the expectation of gap fill before trend resumption.",
  "lessons": "In a bearish trend, prioritize unmitigated FVGs at market extremes as high-probability zones for short entries after price fills them; always require a prior BOS or CHoCH for validity.",
